City Power customers won’t be in the dark this weekend, the utility announced yesterday, after it managed to avoid stage 2 load shedding earlier in the week. This week, following Eskom’s announcement that stage 2 load shedding would be implemented from Thursday evening, City Power took to Twitter to reassure its customers that their lights would remain on. This was because, according to the utility, City Power had extra capacity to help mitigate against load shedding and offset the 200MW which Eskom sought to save. But how did City Power perform the miracle of offsetting the 200MW of load shedding...